Class CheckSoyDocVisitor

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:
NodeVisitor<SoyNode,Void>
public class CheckSoyDocVisitor
extends AbstractSoyNodeVisitor<Void>

Visitor for checking that in each template, the parameters declared in the SoyDoc match the data keys referenced in the template.

Also checks for unnecessary usages of hasData().

Important: Do not use outside of Soy code (treat as superpackage-private).

Precondition: All template and callee names should be full names (i.e. you must execute PrependNamespacesVisitor before executing this visitor).

Note this visitor only works for code in Soy V2 syntax.

AbstractNodeVisitor.exec(N) should be called on a full parse tree. There is no return value. However, a SoySyntaxException is thrown if the parameters declared in some template's SoyDoc do not match the data keys referenced in that template.
